items.title: Porcello stifles Rays as Sox keep 3-game lead
items.summary: Rick Porcello kept the Rays bats in check for 7 1/3 innings and received enough run support to lead the Red Sox to a 3-1 win over the Rays on Saturday night at Tropicana Field.
items.content: Rick Porcello kept the Rays bats in check for 7 1/3 innings and received enough run support to lead the Red Sox to a 3-1 win over the Rays on Saturday night at Tropicana Field.

items.title: JBJ, E-Rod out to lift Sox over Rays in finale
items.summary: Center-field rivals Kevin Kiermaier and Jackie Bradley Jr. match up one last time in 2017 as the Rays and Red Sox wrap up their season series Sunday at Tropicana Field. Tampa Bay righty Jake Odorizzi will oppose Boston lefty Eduardo Rodriguez.
